In order to help us better understand your request for a barrier; please visit the link below to download a request form to provide some background information on your request. Upon receipt of the completed form  engineering staff will review the form and any supporting documentation and perform a site visit for a safety evaluation. Based on the information provided and the site evaluation  we will determine what safety measures (if any) can be implemented in response to your request.     Please note that the completion of this form does not guarantee a barrier will be installed. Other safety measures such as signage  lighting  and/or changes to roadway geometry may also be implemented to address safety concerns instead of  or in addition to  your request for a barrier.    If you have any questions  please contact the Public Works Department Engineering Division at 617-635-4968 or at pwdengineering@boston.gov.
